# Add Property to {{.EntityName}}

## Arguments
- `property-name`: Name of the property (camelCase)
- `type`: One of: string, integer, int64, boolean, number, array

## Steps

### Step 1: Update catalog.yaml

Add the property under `spec.entity.properties`:

```yaml
spec:
  entity:
    name: {{.EntityName}}
    properties:
      # ... existing properties ...
      - name: <property-name>
        type: <type>
        required: false  # optional
```

### Step 2: Regenerate Code

```bash
catalog-gen generate
make gen/openapi-server
```

### Step 3: Update YAML Provider (if using YAML source)

Edit `internal/catalog/providers/yaml_provider.go`:

1. Add field to `yaml{{.EntityName}}` struct
2. Add mapping in `parse{{.EntityName}}Catalog()` function

### Step 4: Update Service Implementation

Edit `internal/server/openapi/api_{{.EntityNameLower}}_service_impl.go`:

Add the property mapping in `convertToOpenAPIModel()`:

```go
if attrs.PropertyName != nil {
    result.PropertyName = *attrs.PropertyName
}
```

### Step 5: Verify

```bash
go build ./...
go test ./...
```
